a_0.formal problem:
theorem
fixes x y :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 33"
and h1 : "y = sqrt 33"
and h2 : "x / y = sqrt 33"
shows  "x / y = sqrt 33"
a_0.formal solution:
(* ### Problem
 Rationalize the denominator of $\displaystyle\frac{33}{\sqrt{33}}$. The final Answer is \!\sqrt{33}
 ### Proof
 $\dfrac{33}{\sqrt{33}} = \dfrac{33}{\sqrt{33}} \cdot \dfrac{\sqrt{33}}{\sqrt{33}} = \dfrac{33\sqrt{33}}{33} = \boxed{\!\sqrt{33}}$.
 *)

theorem
fixes x y :: real
assumes h0 : "x = 33"
and h1 : "y = sqrt 33"
and h2 : "x / y = sqrt 33"
shows  "x / y = sqrt 33"
 proof- 
  show ?thesis sledgehammer
